  "prompt": "Why do I see the same questions in my Quora feed even if I refresh?",
  "response": "Seeing the same questions in your Quora feed even after refreshing can happen for several reasons. Here are some possible explanations:\n\n### 1. **Limited New Content**\n   - Quora's algorithm may not have enough new or relevant content to show you at that moment, especially if your interests are niche or if you\u2019ve already consumed most of the recent posts in your chosen topics.\n\n### 2. **Engagement-Based Prioritization**\n   - Quora prioritizes questions and answers that are popular, have high engagement, or are relevant to your interests. If those questions are still trending or highly engaged with, they might reappear in your feed.\n\n### 3. **Caching or Technical Issues**\n   - Sometimes, the app or website might cache content temporarily, causing the same posts to appear even after a refresh. Clearing your cache or restarting the app could help.\n\n### 4. **Narrow Topic Selection**\n   - If you follow a small number of topics or specific individuals, the pool of available content might be limited, leading to repetition.\n\n### 5. **Advertisements or Sponsored Content**\n   - Quora sometimes inserts advertisements or sponsored content into your feed, which may reappear frequently regardless of your activity.\n\n### 6. **Algorithm Learning**\n   - Quora\u2019s algorithm might still be learning your preferences, especially if you\u2019re a new user. Until it fully understands your interests, it might show you repetitive or broad content.\n\n### 7. **Time of Day**\n   - Activity on Quora fluctuates throughout the day. During periods of low activity, fewer new questions are posted, so the same content may persist in your feed.\n\n### 8. **Interaction History**\n   - If you\u2019ve interacted with a question (e.g., viewed, upvoted, or commented), Quora might think you\u2019re interested in it and show it again.\n\n### What You Can Do:\n   - **Follow More Topics:** Broaden your interests to increase the variety of content in your feed.\n   - **Hide Repetitive Posts:** Use the \u201cHide\u201d or \u201cNot Interested\u201d option to tell Quora you don\u2019t want to see certain content.\n   - **Adjust Notifications:** Customize your notification settings to focus on specific topics or users.\n   - **Clear Cache:** If it\u2019s a technical issue, clearing your cache or updating the app might help.\n\nIf the issue persists, it might be worth reaching out to Quora\u2019s support team for further assistance.",
